Sports ReporterTHE Zimbabwe women s rugby team finished third at the Africa Cup Women s Rugby tournament after they were defeated 31-5 by Kenya in the semi-finals at Morris Depot on Sunday. Zimbabwe took bronze. The Lady Cheetahs started the tournament well, winning two games out of three on Saturday, to book a place in the semis. South Africa won the event after they defeated Kenya 22-17 in a lively final.Charity Macucuti, the Lady Cheetahs captain, hailed the tournament and said they learnt a lot. It was a good tournament, which we enjoyed, every moment, the girls started slowly, but we managed to recover and won some big games. We have a good junior policy and our future is bright, said Macucuti.